<subSubSection pageId="122" pageNumber="123" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
94. 
<taxonomicName LSID="AC6AE297-E5A0-5F34-A7CE-0FB6D55259FA" authority="Franch., Sert. Somal. 41. 1882. (Franchet 1882: 41)." authorityName="Franch., Sert. Somal. 41. 1882. (Franchet" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus capituliferus" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capituliferus">Convolvulus capituliferus Franch., Sert. Somal. 41. 1882. (Franchet 1882: 41).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="122" pageNumber="123" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
SOMALIA, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Recoil</emphasis>
73 (holotype P).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="122" pageNumber="123" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
Annual or briefly perennial herb with a small tap root, similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; stems usually numerous, decumbent or ascending from the base to 40 cm, but usually much less; vegetative parts pubescent. Leaves subsessile, 0.5-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-1.8 cm, oblong or, less commonly, oblanceolate or elliptic, obtuse and sometimes mucronulate, entire, cuneate at the base into an indistinct petiole. Flowers many, in subsessile, bracteate heads forming an elongate leafy inflorescence; peduncles 0-0.4 mm; bracteoles 4-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-3 mm, linear, oblong-elliptic or lanceolate, acute, ciliate especially in the lower half; sepals 5-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-2.5 mm, ovate, acute, pilose and strongly ciliate, the outer sepals c. 1 mm wider than the inner ones; corolla blue, 7-12 mm long, shallowly lobed, midpetaline bands with a few inconspicuous hairs; ovary glabrous, style glabrous, divided 2.5 mm above base, stigmas linear, 2-3 mm, slightly widened towards apex and sometimes unequal. Capsule glabrous, seeds papillate. [
<bibRefCitation author="Verdcourt, B" editor="Hubbard, CE" journalOrPublisher="HMSO, London" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="1 - 161" refId="B373" refString="Verdcourt, B, 1963. Convolvulaceae. In: Hubbard, CE, Milne-Redhead, E, Eds., Flora of Tropical East Africa. HMSO, London: 1 - 161" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Tropical East Africa." year="1963">Verdcourt 1963</bibRefCitation>
: 40 (as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 
<bibRefCitation author="Verdcourt, B" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="459 - 464" publicationUrl="10.2307/4110047" refId="B375" refString="Verdcourt, B, 1982. Corrections and additions to the &quot;Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V. Kew Bulletin 37: 459 - 464, DOI: 10.2307/4110047" title="Corrections and additions to the &quot; Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V." url="10.2307/4110047" volume="37" year="1982">Verdcourt 1982</bibRefCitation>
: 461; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sebsebe, D" editor="Hedberg, I" journalOrPublisher="National Herbarium Addis Ababa University &amp; Department of Systematic Botany, Uppsala University" pageId="211" pageNumber="212" pagination="161 - 231" refId="B330" refString="Sebsebe, D, 2006. Convolvulaceae. In: Hedberg, I, Ensermu, K, Edwards, S, Sebsebe, Demissew, Persson, E, Eds., Flora of Ethiopia &amp; Eritrea 5: Gentianaceae to Cyclocheilaceae. National Herbarium Addis Ababa University &amp; Department of Systematic Botany, Uppsala University: 161 - 231" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Ethiopia &amp; Eritrea 5: Gentianaceae to Cyclocheilaceae." year="2006">Sebsebe 2006</bibRefCitation>
181]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="122" pageNumber="123" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
This species is quite variable, approaching 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verdc., Kew Bull. 12: 344. 1957. (Verdcourt" authorityYear="1957" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus jefferyi" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jefferyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus jefferyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chiov., Fl. Somala 1: 229. 1929. (Chiovenda" authorityYear="1929" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus stenocladus" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stenocladus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus stenocladus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see discussion under both species) at one extreme and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the other. Specimens without corollas cannot be safely separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Following 
<bibRefCitation author="Verdcourt, B" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="459 - 464" publicationUrl="10.2307/4110047" refId="B375" refString="Verdcourt, B, 1982. Corrections and additions to the &quot;Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V. Kew Bulletin 37: 459 - 464, DOI: 10.2307/4110047" title="Corrections and additions to the &quot; Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V." url="10.2307/4110047" volume="37" year="1982">Verdcourt (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, we recognise two infraspecific taxa, their extremes being very different in appearance:
</paragraph>
